text: Mary Anne Marchino (January 27, 1938 - January 29, 2021) was an American competition swimmer. She represented the United States at the 1956 Summer Olympics in Melbourne, Australia. Marchino competed in the qualifying heats of the women's 100-meter backstroke. Marchino wasd born in Indianapolis, Indiana. Marchino died on January 29, 2021 at the age of 83. ==References== Category:1938 births Category:2021 deaths Category:American swimmers Category:Olympians for the United States Category:Sportspeople from Indianapolis
